Version Log
v0.2.0

Split the monolithic script into modules (main.py, cli.py, filters.py, etc.).

Introduced package structure (ropfilter/ with __init__.py).

v0.2.1

Hardened __init__.py and imports for reliability.

Fixed relative import issues.

v0.2.2

Added missing output.py (previously caused ModuleNotFoundError).

v0.2.3

Updated main.py so the tool can run both:

python3 ropfilter/main.py
python3 -m ropfilter


Added sys.path bootstrap fix.

v0.2.4

Fixed UnboundLocalError: parse_imm in classify.py (caused by nested import).

Cleaned classifier imports.

v0.2.5

Expanded CLI help and usage examples.

Added richer descriptions in --help output.

v0.2.6

Implemented reg_match() with support for:

Inclusion sets (eax|ebx).

Exclusion sets (!eax|ebx).

Wildcards (*, any).

Replaced equality checks in filters with reg_match.

v0.2.7

Documented the new ! / | syntax in CLI help.

Updated EPILOG examples.

Version bump to advertise new syntax.

v0.2.8

Added multi-file input awareness:

-f accepts multiple gadget dump files.

Each Gadget tagged with .source.

Output (text, json, python) shows the originating file.

v0.2.9

Fixed printing of score when it was a tuple (TypeError before).

Made output.py:gadget_to_text robust to ints, floats, tuples.

v0.2.10

Changed return ranking order:

0 = clean ret

1 = retn imm

2 = no ret

Fixed disp_rank to only consider memops that match the user’s filters.

Added debug printing of ranking components (disp_rank, ret_rank, instr count, key).

v0.2.11

Introduced strict-mem filtering (default ON).

Rejects gadgets with unconstrained memory references (absolute or unrelated bases).

Only allows [esp±disp] / [ebp±disp] if no mem specs given.

If mem specs exist, only mem ops matching those specs are allowed.

Works across all gadget types (reg2reg, arith, etc.).

Can be disabled with --no-strict-mem.

Hardened strict-mem to also scan arith instructions (inc [esi+...], xor eax,[abs+edx*4]).

v0.2.15

--call-mem now matches all bracketed/sized forms (e.g. call [eax], call dword [eax+4], call qword ptr [ecx]), via SIZEPTR_BRACKET_RE in classify.py.

--arith gains unary neg (both neg reg and neg [mem]) and recognizes memory operands on either side (dst_mem for add [eax], ecx and src_mem for add eax, [ebx]).

--arith filter extended with new keys: dst_base/src_base and dst_abs/src_abs to target memory operands precisely.

Strict memory guard updated to honor --call-mem + arith mem keys, so legit mem gadgets aren’t dropped just for having [ ... ].

Sub-registers (al/ah/ax, bl/bh/bx, etc.) now normalize to parent 32-bit regs (e.g., al → eax) so filters like src=al work.

parse_kvlist() now accepts commas or whitespace between key=value pairs, so --arith 'op=add dst_base=eax src=al' is valid.

Help text (cli.py EPILOG) expanded to list all supported --arith ops and full --memread/--memwrite usage with examples.

Version bumped to 0.2.15 in __init__.py.

v0.2.14 (baseline from your tarball)

Core parsing/classification for reg2reg, memread/memwrite (mov/movzx/movsx forms), arith (binary: add/sub/xor/or/and/adc/sbb/imul; plus lea/movimm/inc/dec recorded), pivots (xchg/mov/add esp, leave), dispatch (call/jmp to reg/mem/abs—mem required plain [reg]).

Filtering layer with bad-byte address filter, reg pattern matching (inclusion/negation/alternation), memread/memwrite specs (dst/src/base/abs), dispatch filters (--call-reg/--call-abs/--call-mem), clobber controls (--avoid-clobber, --require-writes), and strict memory guard default-ON.

CLI features: input via -f, ranking/output controls (e.g., --best-last), base address printing (--base-addr), and a register transfer map view (--reg-map) for quick reg2reg coverage.

Constants include banned instruction patterns to pre-exclude unsafe gadgets; utils include canonical register normalization (32-bit set), immediate parsing, and memory operand parsing.


v0.2.16
reg-map: exclude gadgets that do not end with RET/RETN (e.g., CALL-terminated). Now the reg-map pool is RET-only.